data.label: Brief:SOV01
value: It is your good fortune to be in the vanguard of the Soviet assault on the United States. Lead your troops through Washington and destroy the most hated symbol of American military power, the Pentagon.
Objective 1: Destroy the Pentagon.

data.label: Brief:SOV02
value: The Americans have foolishly gathered a fleet in a small harbor on the eastern coast of Florida. Assisted by General Vladimir in his Dreadnought, you will force a landing on the hostile shore and set up a base. When ready, you will strike out against the capitalist pigs and crush them under the iron heel of Soviet justice.
Objective 1: Force a landing and set up a base.
Objective 2: Destroy all enemy forces.

data.label: Brief:SOV03
value: In order to complete our psychic beacon, we will need to capture some American technology. Lead your forces into New York and capture their Battle Lab. Then build a Psychic Beacon to take control of the city.
Objective 1: Capture the American Battle Lab.
Objective 2: Build and defend a Psychic Beacon.

data.label: Brief:SOV04
value: The foolish Koreans have decided to take sides with the failing Allies. Their cowardly attempt to invade our Eastern territories will surely fail. Defend the motherland and, when you are ready, push the Koreans back into the ocean.
Objective 1: Establish a base. Defend the homeland.
Objective 2: Destroy all enemy forces.

data.label: Brief:SOV05
value: The European nations are planning to join with the crippled Americans. We must not let this act of aggresion go unpunished. You will lay waste to their beautiful Paris. We will show the Allies the true meaning of power by turning their own precious monuments into weapons of mass destruction.
Objective 1: Energize the PARIS TOWER with 3 TESLA TROOPERS.
Objective 2: Defend the PARIS TOWER from Allied attack.
Objective 3: Defeat all remaining Allied troops.

data.label: Brief:SOV06
value: The Americans are on their knees, begging for mercy. The last remnants of their fleet at Pearl Harbor waits helplessly for your relentless attack. However, we have news that the Koreans are not yet beaten and may attempt to join up with the American Navy. They must not succeed.
Objective 1: Establish a base in the Hawaiian Islands.
Objective 2: Destroy the Allied Navy.

data.label: Brief:SOV07
value: The Americans have engaged their Chronosphere; a device that allows them to move soldiers across great distances almost instantly. They can now strike anywhere they wish. You must defend our Battle Lab in the Ural mountains. The Americans will surely strike there soon in a desperate but doomed attempt to shut down our development of the ultimate battle tank.
Objective 1: Defend your Battle Lab at all costs.

data.label: Brief:SOV08
value: Even in the hour of our greatest victory, General Vladimir has turned against us. Tempted by the soft American lifestyle, he has gone rogue and convinced many loyal communists to turn against us. You must go to Washington DC and dig Vladimir out of his wretched hole.
Objective 1: Capture the White House.

data.label: Brief:SOV09
value: Our victory is near at hand. The President has successfully eluded us, but we have tracked him to a dirty little fort called 'The Alamo' in San Antonio, Texas. You must use our Psi-Corp Troopers to mind control the President and force him to surrender the United States.
Objective 1: Use Mind-Control to capture the President.

data.label: Brief:SOV10
value: In their final desperate hours, the Allies have managed to produce one last bit of super-technology. They have a Weather Control Device which they can use to create terrible storms that can sink fleets and level cities. We believe they have hidden their doomsday weapon in the isolated US Virgin Islands.
Objective 1: Capture the American Battle Lab to locate the Weather Control Device.
Objective 2: Destroy the Weather Control Device.

data.label: Brief:SOV11
value: Yuri has turned against us. There is only one answer for such treason.
Objective 1: Destroy Yuri's headquarters - The Kremlin.

data.label: Brief:SOV12
value: We have found the last feeble Allied stronghold. Their Chronosphere, now fully operational, can move soldiers anywhere in the world. They can strike at us in New York, in Prague, even in Moscow. Yuri's files show the device is located near Point Hope, Alaska. You must take what few forces we have in the area and lead an attack, before the Allies make use of their cowardly technology. This is the final hour, commander. Glory awaits.
Objective 1: Destroy the Chronosphere.

data.label: Brief:ALL01
value: The Soviets have invaded. They outnumber us ten to one. You must assist special agent Tanya in New York. We are marshaling our forces as fast as we can, Commander, but we need time. A small American base, Fort Bradley, is in the New York area. If you can make contact, they may be able to assist in the defense of New York. Tanya will be moving through a chaotic battlefield. Keep your eye out for targets of opportunity and watch for new mission objectives.
Objective 1: Destroy the Soviet Dreadnought fleet.
Objective 2: Make contact with Fort Bradley.
Objective 3: Keep Tanya alive.

data.label: Brief:ALL02
value: Soviet troops cover America like a foul plague. They have even penetrated our heartland to capture the Air Force Academy in Colorado. The Academy, its cadets, and the unique technology it contains are vital to our defense. Use Tanya to contact any American forces in the area, reclaim our Air Force Academy, and drive the Soviets from the area.
Objective 1: Capture the Soviet-occupied Air Force Academy Chapel.
Objective 2: Destroy all Soviet forces.
Objective 3: Keep Tanya alive.

data.label: Brief:ALL03
value: The Soviets have invaded Washington DC and have used their evil psychic technology to mind control our leaders. You must rescue them by destroying the Psychic Beacon near the White House.
Objective 1: Destroy the Psychic Beacon.

data.label: Brief:ALL04
value: Soviet forces continue to rampage across America. Our agents have discovered a large Psychic Amplifier in Chicago. If activated, this device will allow the Soviets to mind control all of North America.
Objective 1: Force a shore landing and establish a base.
Objective 2: Destroy the Psychic Amplifier before it comes online.

data.label: Brief:ALL05
value: European forces still refuse to fight with us, fearing a Soviet nuclear counterattack. We have discovered the location of their medium-range missiles in Poland. Special agent Tanya has secretly crossed the Polish border. You will direct her to destroy the Soviet Nuclear Missiles.
Objective 1: Infiltrate the Soviet Battle Lab.
Objective 2: Neutralize the 2 Soviet Nuclear Missile Silos.
Objective 3: Keep Tanya alive.

data.label: Brief:ALL06
value: The Europeans have joined with us and the time has come to counterattack. We will retake Washington DC and then we will retake the rest of our nation from the Soviet scum.
Objective 1: Reinforce and assume command of Allied forces at the Pentagon.
Objective 2: Destroy all Soviet forces in Washington.

data.label: Brief:ALL07
value: The Soviets still cover most of the globe. We must continue to fight them wherever they may be. A Soviet fleet has been discovered en route to Hawaii. Destroy this fleet and the Pacific will be ours.
Objective 1: Destroy all Soviet forces.

data.label: Brief:ALL08
value: Even as we cleanse America of Soviet forces, they continue to play with their psychic technology, desperately hoping that their little toys will destroy us. We have discovered a Psychic Beacon in St. Louis. Take special agent Tanya in and destroy the beacon.
Objective 1: Destroy the Soviet Psychic Beacon.
Objective 2: Destroy all Soviet forces within St. Louis.
Objective 3: Don't get Tanya killed.

data.label: Brief:ALL09
value: The Soviets captured one of our west coast bases and with it one of our Prism Towers. We believe they may be trying to replicate that technology at a secret Soviet research facility in the Yucatan. A SEAL strike team is standing by, Commander, awaiting your orders.
Objective 1: Capture or Destroy any Soviet attempts to replicate our Prism Technology.
Objective 2: Eradicate the Soviet base defending their research site.

data.label: Brief:ALL10
value: Desperate for some success, Soviet forces have counterattacked our European allies in Germany, moving deep into the Black Forest. No doubt their commanders hope that they will find and capture Einstein's laboratory. Your special talents have been asked for. The Germans fear they will be defeated without your strategic skills.
Objective 1: Ensure the safety of Professor Einstein's laboratory.
Objective 2: Destroy all Soviet forces.

data.label: Brief:ALL11
value: Einstein has found the perfect place for his Chronosphere. Unfortunately this location is very close to Soviet-controlled Cuba. Build the Chronosphere and clear the area of Soviet nuclear missiles. We are nearly ready for our final attack on Moscow.
Objective 1: Build a Chronosphere.
Objective 2: Neutralize the Soviet Nuclear threat on Cuba.

data.label: Brief:ALL12
value: The war is nearly at an end. A hand-picked group of volunteers will use the Chronosphere to invade Moscow from across the world. Once you have secured the Kremlin, Tanya will capture Romanov and put an end to Soviet aggression. You are the only commander skilled enough to make this work. Your forces will be outnumbered at least ten to one. Good luck.
Objective 1: Clear the area so Chrono Reinforcements can arrive.
Objective 2: Eliminate Romanov's Elite Black Guard around the Kremlin.

data.label: Brief:TRN02
data.value: This is the last day of your basic training. Time is short and the Soviets may attack soon. Listen to your sergeant, learn what you can, and prepare for battle.

data.label: VOX:cevau01
data.value: Like our own Construction Vehicle, the Soviets can use this MCV to place base anywhere.

data.label: VOX:cevau02
data.value: The Soviet War Miner can easily hold off a small attack force. When hunting down the War Miner, send plenty of fire-power.

data.label: VOX:cevau03
data.value: Simple Soviet technology. The Rhino Heavy Tank is slow, heavily armored and fitted with a devestating short range cannon.

data.label: VOX:cevau04
data.value: The Soviet Terror Drone can easily penetrate the armor of our vehicles. Once inside a vehicle the Terror Drone will destroy it slowly from within. The only way to get a Terror Drone out of a vehicle is to move it to a Service Depot.

data.label: VOX:cevau05
data.value: The Flak Track is standard Soviet air defense. Like all Soviet technology, it is slow and well armored.

data.label: VOX:cevau06
data.value: The V3 is a powerful long-range artillery weapon. Beware commander, it can level your base in minutes without you ever getting a chance to even return fire.

data.label: VOX:cevau07
data.value: The most powerful Soviet Tank ever built, the Apocalpyse is a small army all by itself and is equipped to handle both ground and air threats.

data.label: VOX:cevau08
data.value: The most powerful air unit ever created, the Kirov can take a beating and drop an almost unlimitted number of heavy iron bombs.

data.label: VOX:cevau09
data.value: The Sea Scorpion makes an excellent raider and can also be used to escort heavy Soviet warships.

data.label: VOX:cevau10
data.value: The Soviets have somehow managed to pacify and control the Giant Squid found in the cold waters of the North Pacific. Beware commander, they can immobilize a ship and pull it under in a matter of minutes.

data.label: VOX:cevau11
data.value: The Soviets use their Typhoon Attack Sub to raid our shipping and make surprise attacks on our fleets.

data.label: VOX:cevau12
data.value: The Armored Transort is meant to carry a large number of troops across an ocean to our shores. It is often filled with Soviet troops and can be difficult to destroy.

data.label: VOX:cevau13
data.value: The ultimate in Soviet long-range bombardment, the Dreadnought is powerful from a distance but can be easily destroyed at close range. The Dreadnought's missiles can also be shot down by patriot missiles.

data.label: VOX:cevau14
data.value: The standard Soviet grunt, the Consript is poorly fed, poorly trained and poorly equipped for combat with your boys.

data.label: VOX:cevau15
data.value: The Soviets have taken Tesla Technology to the final step, a man in a Tesla powered suit. These soldiers are excellent at destroying tanks and also seem to be able to power up Tesla Coils with their extra energy.

data.label: VOX:cevau16
data.value: The Soviet Engineer is effective though he is more poorly trained than his American counter-part.

data.label: VOX:cevau17
data.value: Beware these Soviet Attack Dogs, they can quickly sniff out our spies and ruin all of our attempts at covert operations.

data.label: VOX:cevau18
data.value: This Soviet lunatic can and will place bombs on just about anything.

data.label: VOX:cevau19
data.value: This soldier is equiped with a nuclear battlesuit. He can irradiate large patches of ground, making them impassible to infantry or light vehicles.

data.label: VOX:cevau20
data.value: The Soviets have been experimenting with Psychic technology with some success. Their elite PsiCorps can cause our own loyal soldiers to turn against us.

data.label: VOX:cevau21
data.value: Sir, our GI is the finest example of standard infantry soldier in the world. Whether deployed or garrisoning a city building, the GI's heavy machine gun can quickly neutralize any enemy infantry threat.

data.label: VOX:cevau22
data.value: This, sir, is our IFV. It is a multipurpose raider capable of boosting the standard weapon capabilities of any infantryman inside.

data.label: VOX:cevau23
data.value: Sir, this is an engineer. He can repair any Allied building and once inside an enemy building turn it to our side. He is much smarter than his Soviet counterpart.

data.label: VOX:cevau24
data.value: Sir, the SEAL is the elite soldier. No enemy is safe from him, whether on land or water.

data.label: VOX:cevau25
data.value: Commander, the spy's ability to mask himself as the enemy and pass through their ranks gives him the needed edge to infiltrate even the most well guarded enemy building. If only they didn't taste so good to their dogs_

data.label: VOX:cevau26
data.value: The Rocketeers are the brave men who strap maneuvering thrusters to their backs and then go out to hunt enemy tanks and air forces. They are very brave.

data.label: VOX:cevau27
data.value: Commander, this is a Chrono Legionnaire. Using Professor Einstein's Chronal technology they teleport next to any enemy and utterly erase them from time.

data.label: VOX:cevau28
data.value: Sir, these superbly trained dolphins are equipped with special array that allows them to concentrate their natural sonar to easily locate enemy submerged vessels or further concentrate their sonar to attack.

data.label: VOX:cevau29
data.value: Although not as well armored as its Soviet counterpart, our Grizzly Battle tank is much faster and packs the same punch.

data.label: VOX:cevau30
data.value: Commander, our Prism Tank is based on the Prof. Einstein's light enhancement process. It is most effective in dealing with the massive force tactics that the Soviets prefer to use.

data.label: VOX:cevau31
data.value: Commander, our Mirage Tank's ability to hide itself among any natural objects around it make it the perfect ambush or covert surveillance vehicle.

data.label: VOX:cevau32
data.value: The Black Hawk helicopter utilizes the most advanced stealth technologies slip past enemy lines without detection on radar.

data.label: VOX:cevau33
data.value: Sir, the Intruder is a VTOL attack aircraft capable of delivery its ordinance on any target package you desire across the combat zone.

data.label: VOX:cevau34
data.value: Another marvel of technology from Professor Einstein's bag of tricks. Our Chrono Miners can teleport safely and quickly straight back home after gathering their ore supply.

data.label: VOX:cevau35
data.value: Commander, our landing craft is capable of quickly ferrying troops and armor across any body of water- wherever you need them- whenever you need them.

data.label: VOX:cevau36
data.value: Commander, our Destroyer is the workhorse of the navy. No naval unit can long hide from it and once detected, it makes short work of the enemy.

data.label: VOX:cevau37
data.value: Commander, there is no airborne threat that can evade the sight or missile of the Aegis Cruiser. It is the premier anti-air weapon.

data.label: VOX:cevau38
data.value: Sir, our Aircraft Carriers are the pride of the Allied navy. In a moments notice, the carrier's planes can take out any target quickly and from a very safe distance.

data.label: VOX:csof082

data.label: VOX:csofu01
data.value: The Soviet Construction Vehicle is essential and should be defended as such. You cannot create a Construction Yard without one.

data.label: VOX:csofu02
data.value: The Allied Chrono Miner may have the greater speed of teleportation but our War Miner is heavily armored and heavily armed making it immune to most harassment attacks.

data.label: VOX:csofu03
data.value: As the backbone of the Soviet assault force, the Rhino Heavy Tank should be used in all forward positions.

data.value: You're not really planning to nuke mother Russia, are you?

data.label: VOX:msbyu05
data.value: Terror Drones are such mindless beasts. Why don't you train an Engineer instead?

data.label: VOX:mscso03
data.value: Now move up the coast. There is a small airfield there where we can build a base and reclaim our captured Kirov airships.

data.label: VOX:mscso04
data.value: They are using the Chronosphere to transport troops into our base! We cannot stop this assault. Attack soon, Commander, or we will be overrun!

data.label: VOX:mt1ds01
data.value: Good morning commander and welcome to basic training. There's a war on so we have to make this a crash course. In front of you is your battlefield control interface. With this interface you can command any soldier on the field. Let's begin with the new recruit you see in the center of your screen. Move him away from his barracks and out into the field. Left click on the soldier to select him. Then left click on empty ground to move him to that location. Try not to get him killed on the way to the shooting range.

data.label: VOX:mt1ds02
data.value: Notice how you can order your soldier to move into the dark area surrounding the base. This shroud indicates areas of the terrain that you have not yet explored.

data.label: VOX:mt1ds03
data.value: Now that you've mastered the difficult task (said sarcastically) of commanding a single soldier, try ordering around a squad. First, select all of the men by left clicking and holding down the mouse button. In this mode you can drag a selection box around all of your men. Select all of the soldiers at once and order them north to the bridge.

data.label: VOX:mt1ds04
data.value: This bridge was destroyed yesterday when the Navy SEALs used it for demolition practice. An engineer is en-route to repair it. When he arrives, left click on him to select him then left click on the repair hut next to the bridge. Once the bridge is repaired, move your men across.

data.label: VOX:mt1ds05
data.value: This is the shooting range. Select your men by drag-selecting a box around the group. Once selected, left click on the targets down range. This will order your men to fire at these targets. Destroy all of the targets.

data.label: VOX:mt1ds06
data.value: Excellent, your men are good shots. There is a row of targets just out of range of your GIs. Double click on one of your men. He will set himself up in a small defensive position. In this mode he can fire at a greater range. Many units have special abilities like this. Now, order him to destroy the remaining targets.

data.label: VOX:mt1ds07
data.value: Notice that one of your men has a special symbol on him when he is selected. This unit is a veteran unit. Veterans are tougher, stronger and can fire more accurately than ordinary soldiers. Double click on the man who is set up in a defense position to order him to move-out. Now order your men to move on down the road.

data.label: VOX:mt1ds08
data.value: In front of you is a derelict American Grizzly Battle Tank. Order your men to destroy the crippled tank.

data.label: VOX:mt1ds09
data.value: It takes your men longer to destroy the tank than the targets at the rifle range. Regular soldiers are not efficient at destroying armored units. In turn, armored units may not be the most effective weapons for destroying dug in infantry. Pick the right unit when facing enemies. Good job today, you have completed an important part of your training.

data.label: VOX:mt1ds10
data.value: Hurry up commander, you're boring me.

data.label: VOX:mt1ds11
data.value: Keep it moving commander, your training has to go quickly, the Reds are already landing on our shores.

data.label: VOX:mt1ds12
data.value: Commander, this is only one soldier. In a few days you will have to command armies. Now left click on him and then left click on open ground to get him moving out of the base.

data.label: VOX:mt2ds01
data.value: Today you will fight a mock battle against another commander. He will command the red team, you will command of the blue team. Select your Mobil Construction Vehicle by left clicking on it and order it to move out of the base. Get it a safe distance away and try to find some open ground.

data.label: VOX:mt2ds02
data.value: Your Mobile Construction Vehicle is now in open ground. Double click on it to deploy a Construction Yard.

data.label: VOX:mt2ds03
data.value: Now that you have a Construction Yard you can begin to build a base. On the right hand side of your screen you can see that the icon for a Power Plant has appeared. Left click on that icon to start construction of the power plant. Notice how your remaining money decreases while the Power Plant is building. Each building has a cost to construct. When the Power Plant is done building, left click on it's image and then left click on an empty area near your Construction Yard. If you see red squares where you are trying to place the power plant then you are either trying to place the Power Plant too far away from your Construction Yard or you are trying to build on uneven ground.

data.label: VOX:mt2ds04
data.value: Good, your base now has power and you are ready to build more structures. Each buiding you construct also has a power cost. If you run short of power for all of your buildings, some will stop working, and others will work inefficiently. Left click on the Ore Refinery Icon on the right hand side of your screen to build a refinery.

data.label: VOX:mt2ds05
data.value: Now that you have placed a Power Plant you can build a barracks. Many buildings and units depend on one another. You cannot build a barracks until you have built a Power Plant. You cannot train soldiers until you have a barracks. Left click on the barracks to start its construction. When it is finished place it on the terrain just like you did with the Refinery and Power Plant.

data.label: VOX:mt2ds06
data.value: On the right hand side of your screen you should see a button that looks like a soldier. When you press that button you will see the different types of soldiers that you can train. Right now all you can train is a GI. Left click on the GI to start training him. Left click multiple times to train a series of GIs.

data.label: VOX:mt2ds07
data.value: Red team may attack soon. Your GIs are armed with rubber bullets for this mission. In real combat they would of course be shooting real bullets.

data.label: VOX:mt2ds08
data.value: Here comes red team, make me proud commander.

data.label: VOX:mt2ds09
data.value: Red team's strike force has been defeated. Now build some more soldiers commander and when you feel you are ready, move them out onto the map. Find Red team's Command Center and destroy it.

data.label: VOX:mt2ds10
data.value: You really weren't ready for red team were you commander? If this had happened against the Soviets, your base would now be in flames. Red team will pull back to give you a chance to build some more troops.

data.label: VOX:mt2ds11
data.value: Good job commander, you have defeated the red team. Your basic training complete.

data.label: VOX:mt2ds12
data.value: Your new Chrono Miner will automatically begin to collect ore.

data.label: VOX:mt2ds13
data.value: WARNING: The Red Team invasion imminent.

data.label: VOX:mt2ds14
data.value: Deploy your GIs near the entrance to your base for a better defense.

data.label: VOX:mt2ds15
data.value: Send your troops to garrison inside the barn for better protection from enemy fire.

data.label: VOX:mt2ds16
data.value: Send your troops to garrison inside civilian structures for better protection from enemy fire.

data.label: VOX:mt2ds17
data.value: Now is not the time for potty breaks, Commander.

data.label: VOX:mt2ds19
data.value: WARNING: The stench of Red Team is in the air.

data.label: VOX:mt2ds20
data.value: Now that you'e mastered the difficult task (said sarcastically) of commanding a single soldier, try ordering around a squad. First, select all of the men by left clicking and holding down the mouse button. In this mode you can drag a selection box around all of your men. Select all of the soldiers at once and order them East to the bridge.

data.label: VOX:mt2ds21
data.value: Notice that one of your men has a special symbol on him when he is selected. This unit is a veteran unit. Veterans are tougher, stronger and can fire more accurately than ordinary soldiers. Double click on the man who is set up in a defense position to order him to move-out. Now order your men to move on up the road.

data.value: Gosh darn it, I need more cash!

data.label: VOX:taubr05
data.value: Perhaps you should surrender, and avoid further bloodshed.

data.value: That was hardly fair, now was it?

data.value: Heads up old boy, here I come.

data.value: How can I fight without money?

data.label: VOX:taucu04
data.value: If you would do something, I might do something.

data.label: VOX:taucu08
data.value: As if there was ever any doubt.

data.value: I have run out of money.

data.label: VOX:taufr02
data.value: I think I may actually attack.

data.label: VOX:taufr03
data.value: I'm getting slaughtered, I will have to surrender in moments.

data.label: VOX:taufr04
data.value: Distract our enemy and I may try something.

data.label: VOX:taufr05
data.value: Surrender! No, I don't mean I surrender. I mean you surrender.

data.label: VOX:taufr07
data.value: Even a trained monkey could execute that maneuver.

data.label: VOX:taufr08
data.value: Are you ready for me to crush you like the bug that you are?

data.label: VOX:tauge02
data.value: The time to attack is now.

data.label: VOX:tauge03
data.value: Send help or you will soon be on your own.

data.label: VOX:tauge04
data.value: Distract him, I have something _clever_ in mind.

data.label: VOX:tauge05
data.value: Surrender, you are all but beaten.

data.label: VOX:tauge07
data.value: I will get you for that.

data.label: VOX:tauir01
data.value: As unbelievable as it may seem, I am out of money.

data.label: VOX:tauir03
data.value: You must send help, don't ask questions, just do as you are told.

data.label: VOX:tauir04
data.value: If you distract our enemy, I will execute my master plan.

data.label: VOX:tauir05
data.value: It will be very boring for me, but perhaps you should surrender.

data.label: VOX:tauir07
data.value: I will make you pay for that.

data.label: VOX:tauir08
data.value: Is not my army beautiful? Behold as it destroys everything you own.

data.label: VOX:tauko02
data.value: My men are ready, soon we will attack.

data.label: VOX:tauko03
data.value: My soldiers are being slaughtered, send help.

data.label: VOX:tauko04
data.value: Distract our enemy commander and I will destroy him.

data.label: VOX:tauko05
data.value: Surrender now and you will live.

data.label: VOX:tauli01
data.value: I seem to be low on money.

data.label: VOX:tauli04
data.value: You must distract our enemies while I make a secret attack.

data.label: VOX:tauli05
data.value: You are beaten! Surrender while you yet have buildings to sell!

data.label: VOX:tauli07
data.value: What was that? You call that a tactic? You disgust me.

data.label: VOX:tauli08
data.value: Look at the battle, your doom is at hand.

data.label: VOX:tauru01
data.value: My resources are taxed to their limits.

data.label: VOX:tauru02
data.value: I will soon crush our enemies.

data.label: VOX:tauru03
data.value: Send me help comrade, before it is too late!

data.label: VOX:tauru04
data.value: Do something you idiot. I have a plan.

data.label: VOX:tauru05
data.value: If you surrender now, perhaps I will kill you quickly.

data.label: VOX:tauru07
data.value: You are fool to try such tactics.

data.label: VOX:tauru08
data.value: There is no escape, there will be no mercy.

data.label: VOX:vdematc
data.value: It will be a smoking crater.

data.value: Your lightning counterattack blunted the Soviet invasion.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgALL01
data.value: You barely succeeded in holding back the Soviet advance.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgALL02
data.value: Your tank blitz stunned the Soviets, ending the battle in a few short hours.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgALL02
data.value: Your grinding assault cost hundreds of lives but liberated the Air Force Academy.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgALL03
data.value: The President was rescued long before the Soviets could discover any important military secrets.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgALL03
data.value: The President was rescued, though many military secrets were compromised.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgALL04
data.value: The tragic loss of Chicago, however devastating, doesn't compare to the loss of our whole nation. Your quick destruction of the Psychic Amplifier meant that the Soviets never had time to fully test its power.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgALL04
data.value: The Psychic Amplifier was destroyed, but not before the Soviets gained valuable test data about it's effects. In spite of the tragic loss of Chicago, however, you've saved our entire nation from falling under the influence of the Soviets' most powerful psychic weapon.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgALL05
data.value: Soviet commanders are still analyzing your attack, trying to discover the secrets of your advanced covert strategies.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgALL05
data.value: The missiles have been destroyed. Other Soviet missiles have been moved deep inside the USSR.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgALL06
data.value: The precision with which you destroyed the Soviet forces and liberated Washington DC is one for the record books.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgALL06
data.value: Washington DC has been saved, but at a terrible price in men and materials.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgALL07
data.value: You defended Pearl Harbor with such ferocity that the Pacific is ours.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgALL07
data.value: Pearl Harbor has been saved, but the Hawaiian islands have been devestated by the Soviet onslaught.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgALL08
data.value: You saved Saint Louis before her citizens could come to any harm.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgALL08
data.value: Saint Louis was saved, but thousands of American citizens were permanently turned to the Soviet cause.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgALL09
data.value: Soviet Soldiers have nicknamed you "The Ghost" for your skills at stealthy destruction.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgALL09
data.value: Thanks to you, our technology has been recovered.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgALL10
data.value: Impressed by your efficiency, German Commanders have asked you to train their officers in strategy and command.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgALL10
data.value: The Black Forest lab has been saved, Einstein's work can continue.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgALL11
data.value: Russian commanders fear your command more than whole Allied divisions. If one man can make a difference, you are that man.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgALL11
data.value: The Chronosphere is built. Thanks to your tireless effort, the Allies are ready for one final push to victory.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgALL12
data.value: Your legendary command skills will go down in history. You are one of the greatest generals of all time.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgALL12
data.value: Romanov is captured, the war is won. Victory is yours.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgSov01
data.value: The Pentagon was crushed so quickly that many important American generals were captured by our victorious soldiers, crippling their armed forces.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgSov01
data.value: Thanks to you, the Pentagon has been destroyed and the American military has been thrown into chaos.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgSov02
data.value: The American fleet and Naval base were destroyed so quickly that your soldiers were able to capture several American officers.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgSov02
data.value: The American fleet was destroyed. While Soviet casualties were high, this is of no concern so long as you continue to bring victory.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgSov03
data.value: The Psychic Beacon was built so quickly that an entire American Armored division was captured by its power before they could escape.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgSov03
data.value: You have spread the power of Premier Romanov. American civilians are eagerly joining our army.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgSov04
data.value: The Korean invasion was repelled with such ferocity that some members of their government have spoken secretly to us of peace.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgSov04
data.value: In a long and bloody battle, you successfully defended mother Russia.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgSov05
data.value: The French fear your command more than they fear our tanks. In Paris you are known only as 'The Butcher'.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgSov05
data.value: You turned the Paris Tower into a weapon of terror. You have 'punished' Europe sufficiently.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgSov06
data.value: Allied Admirals now refuse to send their ships to sea, so quick was your destruction of Pearl Harbor.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgSov06
data.value: The Koreans and Americans have been successfully divided. The Pacific is ours.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgSov07
data.value: Your ruthless efficiency has earned you great respect in the Red Army and made Soviet leadership fear your popularity.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgSov07
data.value: The battle lab is safe. The Allies will not dare strike inside mother Russia again.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgSov08
data.value: Traitors beware: Your sudden and righteous attack on Washington D.C. has made your rivals fear your strategic skills.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgSov08
data.value: Vladimir has been punished for his crimes. Your victory has not gone unnoticed in this dark hour.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgSov09
data.value: World leaders tremble in fear at the mention of our psychic troops. With you in command, no one is safe.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgSov09
data.value: The President is ours to command. You will be rewarded for your zeal.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgSov10
data.value: Your strategic skills are becoming legendary. It is openly said among the men that it is you alone that will bring them victory.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgSov10
data.value: The Allies cannot hold out much longer against your heavy-handed assaults. You use the lives of your men well.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgSov11
data.value: Already your name is known to school children as the greatest general the world has ever known.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgSov11
data.value: Yuri's defenses were weak and feeble. Your tank divisions swept him aside as you have swept aside so many others.

data.label: GUI:UnderParMsgSov12
data.value: History will name you among the greatest commanders that has ever lived. Now the world is yours to rule.

data.label: GUI:OverParMsgSov12

data.label: COOP:Camp11
data.value: The Soviets have invaded Texas! Stop them.

data.label: COOP:Camp11v
data.value: Commander's Log -Texas, USA: The first Soviet unit to enter the United States was the Russian 2nd Motorized Rifle Division. They quickly set up bases in Southern Texas from which they could strike at US strategic assets all across the Southwest. American forces were quickly overwhelmed and it soon looked as though Russian and Cuban divisions would occupy all major cities in the southern US. Only a few diehard American commanders stood in the way.

data.label: COOP:Camp12
data.value: Soviet and Cuban forces are striking into Alabama. Destroy them.

data.label: COOP:Camp12v
data.value: Commander's Log - Alabama, USA: In the 2nd week of the war, despite massive loses, Soviet and Cuban forces attempted to link their battle lines in Alabama. Though their resources were nearly depleted, American commanders managed to put up a stiff resistance.

data.label: COOP:Camp13
data.value: Cuban forces have invaded Florida. Push them back into the sea.

data.label: COOP:Camp13v
data.value: Commander's Log - Florida, USA: While Russian forces raged across the Old South, Cuban forces quickly invaded Florida. Their first attacks were successful, however the Cubans met with grass-roots resistance when American commanders managed to procure a few MCVs from European blockade-runners.

data.label: COOP:Camp14
data.value: Soviet forces threaten Atlanta. Find and destroy their supply base.

data.label: COOP:Camp14v
data.value: Commander's Log - Georgia, USA: In the 4th week of the war, Russian and Cuban forces gathered in the Georgian countryside. Their mission was simple, gather resources, replenish two badly damaged Soviet divisions and then rage into the undefended city of Atlanta. The Soviet policy was clear, resistance must be punished and the American rebels must be taught a lesson. Before the Soviets were ready, a British spy sent word of the attack to American Commanders and battle was joined.

data.label: COOP:Camp15
data.value: The Soviets have a network of bases along the Mexican border. Destroy them to end the war.

data.label: COOP:Camp15v
data.value: Commander's Log - Texas, USA: As the Soviets were pushed back out of the United States, the last survivors of the battle for Texas laid siege to a mighty Russian battle fortress on the Mexican border. From this base the Soviets could make air and nuclear strikes deep into the United States. The Soviet base had to be destroyed, no matter what the price.

data.label: COOP:Camp21
data.value: Strike a blow for freedom, your forces are in Romania, destroy all Soviet forces.

data.label: COOP:Camp21v
data.value: Commander's Log - Eastern Europe: While the Soviets were striking against America, the Europeans remained silent. When the Soviets nuked Chicago, the Europeans prayed the war would not come to their shores, but when the Soviets attacked Paris, even the most cautious commander knew that the time had come for war. It was a combined French and German force that struck the first blow into Eastern Europe, led by the most aggressive European commanders on the continent.

data.label: COOP:Camp22
data.value: The Soviets have counterattacked into Germany. You must hold the line.

data.label: COOP:Camp22v
data.value: Commander's Log - Eastern Europe: Despite their initial success, the Allies soon found themselves surrounded on all sides by entrenched Soviet forces. Soviet units quickly cut off any chance of retreat in Romania and the Allied expeditionary force was forced to fight their way back to friendly battle lines.

data.label: COOP:Camp23
data.value: You have been ordered to seize control of the Black Sea and her harbors.

data.label: COOP:Camp23v
data.value: Commander's Log - Romania: As weeks stretched into months, the Allies tired as Europe was once again a grim battleground for the most powerful nations on earth. Eager to take the battle to the enemy, the Allies sent their best commanders into the Mediterranean to seize control of vital island strongholds and prepare large fleets for an attack into the Black Sea.

data.label: COOP:Camp24
data.value: In a surprise attack, your forces have been sent into Poland. Crush the unprepared Soviets.

data.label: COOP:Camp24v
data.value: Commander's Log - Poland: With the Soviets distracted by a major amphibious landing on their own shores, Allied forces seized the opportunity to make a major armored attack into Poland. In the 4th month the Allies lead their forces across the Rhine at the dead of night in the middle of winter, taking the Soviet bases completely by surprise.

data.label: COOP:Camp25
data.value: The drive into Russia has begun. Your forces are in the Ukraine and face a desperate Red Army.

data.label: COOP:Camp25v
data.value: Commander's Log - Ukraine, Soviet Union: With most of Europe still weak from battle, two European commanders took it upon themselves to put an end to the war in Europe by striking against the main Soviet Headquarters inside the Russian border. Without authorization or approval from their governments, these commanders gathered what forces remained and struck what they hoped would be a final blow.

data.label: COOP:Camp31
data.value: Destroy all Soviet forces along the Sea of Japan.

data.label: COOP:Camp31v
data.value: Commander's Log - Japan: The Korean government remained neutral during the first few months of the war until a Korean reporter learned that the Soviets had used Psychic Technology to mind control key members of the Korean leadership. When the story broke Korea went to war, and her commanders were to fight in almost every country in the Far East. The first attack took the Soviets almost completely by surprise as the Koreans fought along the coast of Japan for naval supremacy of the Pacific.

data.label: COOP:Camp32v
data.value: Commander's Log - Vietnam: As the Soviets continued to spread across South East Asia, consuming the small countries that stood in their way, the Korean Army dispatched two divisions to Vietnam to defend it against a major Soviet strike force. The Korean commanders were outnumbered almost two to one and knew that only superior leadership would save them from certain defeat.

data.label: COOP:Camp33
data.value: Your home nation, Korea is threatened, defend your lands at any cost.

data.label: COOP:Camp33v
data.value: Commander's Log - Republic of Korea: Three weeks after declaring war on the Soviet Union, Korean commanders faced an invasion of their own country by a secret Soviet division hidden from their intelligence network by powerful psychic technology. Using what forces remained in country the Koreans marched to their own border and prepared to make the Soviets pay for every inch of ground.

data.label: COOP:Camp34
data.value: Invade the frozen wastes of eastern Russia and destroy the Soviet bases.

data.label: COOP:Camp34v
data.value: Commander's Log - Harbin, Soviet Union: With most of the Soviet forces in the Far East neutralized or destroyed the Korean High Command ordered their generals to take the fight to the enemy and Korean forces invaded the frozen wastes of Eastern Russia.

data.label: COOP:Camp35
data.value: Complete your invasion of Siberia and destroy the Soviet supply bases that fuel war effort.

data.label: COOP:Camp35v
data.value: Commander's Log - Siberia, Soviet Union: Despite massive losses to battle and the bitter cold, the Korean invasion force was not deterred and moved quickly against the oil fields of eastern Siberia. With the invasion in America going poorly for the Soviets and the European Allies attacking into Russia herself, the Koreans had a unique opportunity to deliver a crippling blow to the Soviet war machine. Korea had a chance to make a huge difference in the overall war.

data.label: COOP:Camp41
data.value: Your legions have invaded Italy. Destroy all who oppose you.

data.label: COOP:Camp41v
data.value: Commander's Log - Italy: While the Russians managed to persuade a few pariah warlord states to join their cause, most were only in the war for their own gain. It was a chance for many warlord nations to prey upon their neighbors, to expand their borders and to seize the resources they needed to maintain their failing economies. While Soviet forces fought around the globe, Iraq and Libya seized the opportunity for a joint invasion of southern Italy. Only a pitiful few French and English forces opposed them.

data.label: COOP:Camp42
data.value: Greece is our next target. Destroy any Allies who dare to oppose our conquest.

data.label: COOP:Camp42v
data.value: Commander's Log - Greece: As the English and French rallied their forces at the Alps the combined forces of the Iraqi and Libyan armies smashed into Greece. The Grecian army was overrun in a matter of days but a combined French and British force brought by boat from India and French Malaysia managed to put up a token resistance.

data.label: COOP:Camp43
data.value: The French and English have counterattacked in Italy. Destroy their advanced bases.

data.label: COOP:Camp43v
data.value: Commander's Log - Italy: Their supply lines overextended and their armies scattered across southern Europe, the Libyans and Iraqis were vulnerable to an Allied counterattack. In the 3rd week of the war the French and English attacked, striking at the ports of southern Italy in an attempt to cut-off Iraqi forces from their naval supply lines.

data.label: COOP:Camp44
data.value: The Allies have paradropped into the fertile plane just outside Baghdad. Destroy them.

data.label: COOP:Camp44v
data.value: Commander's Log - Iraq: After their failed attack, the Allies tried one last desperate gamble in the 4th week of the war. While Libyan death squads hunted down Allied troops in the Italy war-zone, the English and French took what forces they had remaining and made a massive airdrop in the fertile river basin outside of Baghdad, hoping to set up bases to siege the city.

data.label: COOP:Camp45
data.value: The French have built a massive fortress in northern Greece. This is the last point of resistance.

data.label: COOP:Camp45v
data.value: Commander's Log - Greece: Assisted by French base defenses, the Allies built a massive fortress in their last remaining stronghold of northern Greece. The French and English held out for nearly three weeks before the Iraqi and Libyan armies sent in their most battle-hardened commanders to find a way to break through the Allied defenses.

data.label: COOP:Camp51
data.value: Destroy the Russian fleets and naval bases in the North Sea.

data.label: COOP:Camp51v
data.value: Commander's Log - North Sea: While the Soviet army was busy crushing American resistance on the Eastern Seaboard, the Soviet Navy fought a bloody battle to cross the North Atlantic and deliver supplies and reinforcements to their troops. The first battles were fought on tiny islands in the North Sea where combined Allied forces attempted to hold back the Soviet battle groups and destroy any bases the Soviets managed to build.

data.label: COOP:Camp52
data.value: The Soviets have invaded Norway. We must save this ally from Soviet dominion.

data.label: COOP:Camp52v
data.value: Commander's Log - Norway: The initial Allied success prompted an immediate and brutal response from the Soviets. Threatened by superior Allied naval forces, the Soviets invaded the neutral countries of Sweden and Norway to lay claim to the warm water ports that would allow them to build large fleets and strike anywhere along the northern coast of Europe. The Allies gathered their best commanders and with only a handful of forces, sent them into Norway to hold back the Soviet horde.

data.label: COOP:Camp53
data.value: A secret Soviet base has been discovered in the British Isles. Destroy it before it is too late.

data.label: COOP:Camp53v
data.value: Commander's Log - British Isles: As the Soviets became more desperate to deliver war materials to their failing armies in America, they began to try more devious means of breaking the Allied blockade in the North Atlantic. In the 3rd month of the war, a small Soviet force made a secret landing in northern Britain and set up a base. By the time the Allies discovered the Soviet presence, it was nearly too late.

data.label: COOP:Camp54
data.value: The Soviets have swept into Germany. Stop their advance and destroy their forces.

data.label: COOP:Camp54v
data.value: Commander's Log - Germany: As the war entered its 4th month the Allies grew bold and began major attacks into Poland from Austria, striking against Soviet bases and liberating thousands of Polish civilians. The Soviets responded quickly with three armored divisions that swept into eastern Germany, cutting off the Allied attackers. The battle quickly degenerated into a chaotic base versus base duel, with the outcome sure to change the course of the war in Europe.

data.label: COOP:Camp55
data.value: Victory is close at hand, destroy the Soviet naval bases in the Baltic to end the war for the North Atlantic.

data.label: COOP:Camp55v
data.value: Commander's Log - Northern Baltic Sea: Victory after victory had brought the Allies into the Northern Baltic where they hoped to destroy the Soviet naval bases that continually reinforced the Soviet North Atlantic fleet. The Allies were only able to spare a few forces from their blockade groups for the assault, leaving them outnumbered three to one in what they hoped would be the final battle of the North Atlantic campaign.
